<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,153,791]" pageId="10" pageNumber="39">
Male specimens above listed have tegmina as long as or just longer than abdomen; they have been collected in the 
<typeStatus box="[193,241,189,215]" pageId="10" pageNumber="39">type</typeStatus>
locality of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Walker" baseAuthorityYear="1870" box="[370,464,189,215]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphagidae" genus="Pagopedilum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevis">
<emphasis box="[370,464,189,215]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="39">P. brevis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, of which only the female nymph was known. Thus, this is the first record of the adult male and female of this species.
</paragraph>
